CYCLOSPORIASIS - USA (02): BACKGROUND
*************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sun 2 Oct 2011
Source: GIDEON (Global Infectious Disease & Epidemiology Network)
[edited]
http://www.gideononline.com


[Re: ProMED-mail Cyclosporiasis - USA: (GA) 20111001.2960]
----------------------------------------------------------
Notwithstanding a recent outbreak in Georgia, _Cyclospora_ is the
least common intestinal protozoan reported in the United States.

In the following graph I have summarized the incidences of
cyclosporiasis, giardiasis, amebiasis, and cryptosporidiosis:
http://www.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Protozoa-US.png.

As indicated at the black arrow, ongoing trends for amebiasis (no
longer reported as of 1994 -- 2983 cases) were "replaced" by reports
of cryptosporidiosis (2972 cases in 1995).

(For outline of Gideon Graph module see
http://www.GIDEONonline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Gideon-Graphs.pps)

Reference
---------
Berger SA: Infectious Diseases of the United States, 2011. 1030 pp,
464 graphs, 8237 references. GIDEON ebooks,
http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-the-united-states.

